\begin_layout Paragraph*

\series medium
The 2D (or traditional) MODE approach to object-base verification enabled
 users to analyze forecasts in terms of location errors, intensity errors
 and shape, size and orientation errors.
 MTD retains all of that capability, and adds new classes of forecast errors
 involving time information: speed and direction errors, buildup and decay
 errors, and timing and duration errors.
 This opens up new ways of analyzing forecast quality.
\end_layout

